results.lead_paragraph: Once it was the Evil Empire. Now it's the Magic Kingdom. As if Russia's problems weren't depressing enough, the country's desperate cash hunger has caused it to turn its vast and impressive military enterprise into a kind of theme park -- with very expensive rides. A new company, MIGS Etc., of Sarasota, Fla., will arrange for tourists to fly, for a price, almost any variety of Russian aircraft, from L-39 training jets to top-of-the-line MIG-29 jet fighters. Customers need not be pilots, let alone fighter pilots; experienced Russian jet jockeys accompany them on all flights. Prices start at $6,000 and go up to $45,000 for a program that involves a simulated dogfight.
